# tools

Tool-side enforcement layer. Every model write passes through this
module; honesty guards and SpecDD Lever 2 Forbids enforcement live here.

## Must
- `write_file` and `edit_file` run honesty guards (role-path, placeholder, mass-deletion) before any I/O
- SpecDD Lever 2 `_check_spec_forbids` runs after honesty guards (cheaper guards first)
- `SddParseError` catch precedes `ValueError` catch in fs.py — `SddParseError` subclasses `ValueError`
- All tool errors return as `(str, str | None)` tuples; never raise to the caller
- `get_repo_root()` is the canonical accessor — never `from luxe.tools.fs import _REPO_ROOT`
- `cve_lookup` is gated to `task_type == "manage"` only (surface bloat regresses implement)
- New honesty-pattern guards land with a regression test in `tests/test_tools.py`

- `bash` defaults to the hardened allowlist + chain/redirect rejection
  (`_validate_command`). The module `TOOL_FNS["bash"]` MUST stay restricted —
  every benchmark/maintain run uses it. The unrestricted variant
  (`make_bash_fn(unrestricted=True)` + `unrestricted_bash_def()`) is reachable
  ONLY via `luxe chat` dev mode (opt-in `/bash`, write-mode only), passed through
  `run_single`'s extra-tool seam; it never becomes the default fn

## Must not
- Bypass `_safe()` path scoping in any new tool
- Hardcode tool-allowlist subsets in `single.py` (the role config is the single source of truth)
- Wire unrestricted bash into the benchmark/maintain path or the default
  `TOOL_FNS` — it is a chat-front-end carve-out only

## Owns
- src/luxe/tools/**
